   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="discussion">
      <p>
Remarks
</p>
      <p>
This genus was originally described from Central Africa (
Uganda
). Examination of 
type
material for 
<tp:taxon-name>
Doryctes
species
</tp:taxon-name>
described by 
Granger (1949)
from 
Madagascar
showed that 
<tp:taxon-name>
D. pilosus
Granger, 1949
</tp:taxon-name>
actually belongs to 
<tp:taxon-name>
Hemispathius
</tp:taxon-name>
(comb. nov.) due to its shorter and wider first metasomal tergite and its shorter acrosternite. This species, characterised by the entirely yellow colouration, is also found in 
Yemen
.
</p>
   </tp:treatment-sec>
